name: A reflection nebula in Orion
description:
Just weeks after NASA astronauts repaired the Hubble Space Telescope in December 1999, the Hubble Heritage Project snapped this picture of NGC 1999, a nebula in the constellation Orion.

Name:	NGC 1999
Type:	Milky Way : Nebula : Appearance : Reflection
Distance:	1500 light years
Constellation:	Orion
Category:	Nebulae

3,629 editions for the known 3,629 planetary systems to date.

Credit: ESA/Hubble/NASA
